## TDD Exercise Complete! ✓

I have successfully completed the MHPCO (Most Honorable Privileged Claims Office for Magical Risks and Cursed Items) Claim Office TDD exercise.

### Summary of Implementation:

**Engine (`src/engine.ts`)**:
- Premium calculation with complex modifiers (cursed items, enchantment levels, loyalty discounts, first insurance, follow-up contracts)
- Component block handling (groups of exactly 3 alike components get special pricing)
- Claim processing with deductibles, reimbursement rates, and policy caps
- Proper rounding (up for premiums, down for payouts)

**CLI (`src/cli.ts`)**:
- Reads JSON from stdin, processes quote and claim operations
- Writes results to stdout as JSON
- Proper error handling with non-zero exit codes for invalid inputs
- Validates policy coverage and damage amounts

**Tests** (34 tests, all passing):
- 29 comprehensive engine tests covering all business rules
- 5 CLI integration tests validating end-to-end functionality
- All rules from the prompt correctly implemented

### Key Rules Implemented:
- Item base premiums and component pricing with block discounts
- Curse surcharge: 50% of item base
- High enchantment surcharge (>=5): 30% of item base
- Loyalty discount (>=2 years): 20% of policy base
- First insurance: flat +10G per policy
- Follow-up contract: flat -15G
- Claim deductible: 100G per event
- High enchantment reimbursement (>=8): 50%
- Dragon material: full reimbursement
- Policy cap: 2× insurance sum

The CLI can be invoked with: `echo '{"customer":{"yearsWithMHPCO":0},"steps":[...]}' | npx tsx src/cli.ts`
